{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 21:53:08.938111", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission complete.\n\nSummary:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): host_2_1_1_1\n- Root cause(s): sender_application_delay\n\nRationale:\n- Automated ping and curl tests on host_2_1_1_1 intermittently timed out, while immediate manual runs succeeded and end-to-end routing/DNS/HTTP paths were healthy. This indicates an execution/tooling delay or glitch on the host rather than a network forwarding failure. \n- Short DHCP lease timers were observed but did not impact connectivity and are attributable to server-side policy, not a fault affecting data plane operations.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2220, "output_tokens": 130, "total_tokens": 2350, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
